<paragraph id="7E5084D6AE5D36711890B3F2BDA58942" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">Published records.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="29C12DD0784C58B0389261CE2918E50B" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">
<bibRefCitation id="E6F002CAC89F888402033B8E20B8FA88" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00963801.60-2413.1" author="Cockerell, TDA" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the United States National Museum" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" pagination="1 - 20" refId="B10" refString="Cockerell, TDA, 1922. Bees in the collection of the United States National Museum. 4. Proceedings of the United States National Museum 60 (2413): 1 - 20, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00963801.60-2413.1" title="Bees in the collection of the United States National Museum. 4." url="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00963801.60-2413.1" volume="60" year="1922">Cockerell 1922</bibRefCitation>
: 12 (Sichuan); 1931: 12 (Shanghai); 
<bibRefCitation id="F4AE202B865CC606496D7D5648ABEB9D" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.792.28042" author="Astafurova, YuV" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" pagination="15 - 44" refId="B3" refString="Astafurova, YuV, Proshchalykin, MYu, Niu, Z-q, Zhu, C-d, 2018. New records of bees of the genus Sphecodes Latreille (Hymenoptera, Halictidae) in the Palaearctic part of China. ZooKeys 792: 15 - 44, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.792.28042" title="New records of bees of the genus Sphecodes Latreille (Hymenoptera, Halictidae) in the Palaearctic part of China." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.792.28042" volume="792" year="2018">Astafurova et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
: 30 (Shanxi, Shaanxi).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="93DF17F1FC67CEFDEABCEE9D1E4DD2EE" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="AFCB6CCFF55701AD103BABB3CD62AB97" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">Remark.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B33AB0394C416524F2730888D42162EA" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">
According to 
<bibRefCitation id="A7709CA53F920706B4AFF81E3AD2F34E" author="Wu, Y-R" journalOrPublisher="Sciense Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" refId="B25" refString="Wu, Y-R, 1965. Hymenoptera: Apoidea, Chinese Economic Insect Fauna, Vol. 9. Sciense Press, Beijing" title="Hymenoptera: Apoidea, Chinese Economic Insect Fauna, Vol. 9." year="1965">Wu (1965)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="9147AB779C4D0F3F0CF2AE4A40F45BBE" author="Wu, Y-R" journalOrPublisher="Kunming, Yunnan Science and Technology Press" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" refId="B26" refString="Wu, Y-R, He, W, Wang, SF, 1988. Bee Fauna of Yunnan. Kunming, Yunnan Science and Technology Press" title="Bee Fauna of Yunnan." year="1988">Wu et al. (1988)</bibRefCitation>
this species was recorded from different provinces of China (Jilin, Hebei, Anhui, Jiangsu, Shandong, Shanghai, Zhejiang, Sichuan, Yunnan, Xizang, Guandong). However, re-identification of specimens from the IZCAS Collection determined by Prof. Wu as 
<taxonomicName id="E8495A6B535D69D622327DA8AA819ED4" genus="S." lsidName="S. grahami" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" rank="species" species="grahami">
<emphasis id="7FF4546A894CE225999E839FE72F83A0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">S. grahami</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as well as the analysis of the descriptive notes given in these works revealed misidentifications. In fact, the specimens from Yunnan (1 â™€, Lijiang) and Sichuan (1 â™‚, Barkam; 1 â™€, Xiangcheng) belong to 
<taxonomicName id="962C8A1FC92C870A94BBAC299D6D7FC1" genus="S." lsidName="S. pieli" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" rank="species" species="pieli">
<emphasis id="1B2E384B5673CA37213929AC7965E869" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">S. pieli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. These two species are very similar structurally and sculpturally, but 
<taxonomicName id="191DD72CF9A32DAADDE19643AD76273D" genus="S." lsidName="S. grahami" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" rank="species" species="grahami">
<emphasis id="EB9747847E124560FBBAD9445EBEFADD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">S. grahami</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs by lack of a longitudinal carina on vertex (also indicated in 
<bibRefCitation id="F5494E9987464149396B694104408386" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00963801.60-2413.1" author="Cockerell, TDA" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the United States National Museum" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" pagination="1 - 20" refId="B10" refString="Cockerell, TDA, 1922. Bees in the collection of the United States National Museum. 4. Proceedings of the United States National Museum 60 (2413): 1 - 20, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00963801.60-2413.1" title="Bees in the collection of the United States National Museum. 4." url="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00963801.60-2413.1" volume="60" year="1922">Cockerell 1922</bibRefCitation>
: 12). In contrast, the longitudinal carina on vertex in 
<taxonomicName id="F4574AB8446F9289A685E19F49290E99" genus="S." lsidName="S. pieli" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" rank="species" species="pieli">
<emphasis id="598828BE398E3E2E1875F18FB1DE9512" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">S. pieli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is clearly developed, corresponding to descriptive notes by 
<bibRefCitation id="D9183E99A3ABE8A779EFC26C8D59367B" author="Wu, Y-R" journalOrPublisher="Sciense Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" refId="B25" refString="Wu, Y-R, 1965. Hymenoptera: Apoidea, Chinese Economic Insect Fauna, Vol. 9. Sciense Press, Beijing" title="Hymenoptera: Apoidea, Chinese Economic Insect Fauna, Vol. 9." year="1965">Wu (1965)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="59B877BA615C992A5BBBB2D5ACF465F0" author="Wu, Y-R" journalOrPublisher="Kunming, Yunnan Science and Technology Press" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" refId="B26" refString="Wu, Y-R, He, W, Wang, SF, 1988. Bee Fauna of Yunnan. Kunming, Yunnan Science and Technology Press" title="Bee Fauna of Yunnan." year="1988">Wu et al. (1988)</bibRefCitation>
, where pointed on &quot;small process on vertex&quot;. Among determined by Wu specimens we have not found any specimens from Xizang, with records from this province (
<bibRefCitation id="117E5B1A795E0F3D1C15EFD7CB884B9F" author="Wu, Y-R" journalOrPublisher="Kunming, Yunnan Science and Technology Press" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" refId="B26" refString="Wu, Y-R, He, W, Wang, SF, 1988. Bee Fauna of Yunnan. Kunming, Yunnan Science and Technology Press" title="Bee Fauna of Yunnan." year="1988">Wu et al. 1988</bibRefCitation>
) instead referring to 
<taxonomicName id="0CC0035F6AC3FDD9031E505A47C1F659" genus="S." lsidName="S. montanus" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" rank="species" species="montanus">
<emphasis id="A685B492743F7CE56919DED461411246" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">S. montanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, another species similar to 
<taxonomicName id="83C427CD40C33148CDCDF3628CD24E62" genus="S." lsidName="S. grahami" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" rank="species" species="grahami">
<emphasis id="053ACFB56725CE3B4A743A83229D4EF7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">S. grahami</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with a vertex carina. So, males of 
<taxonomicName id="5BC686FE52D8CC4D776C3A780FE6D951" genus="S." lsidName="S. grahami" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" rank="species" species="grahami">
<emphasis id="28227E36DA98483E3F94320F0FD319F2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">S. grahami</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
recorded by Wu, 1965 and 
<bibRefCitation id="180C18DDD8B59CD19D09D282CD94E1F7" author="Wu, Y-R" journalOrPublisher="Kunming, Yunnan Science and Technology Press" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" refId="B26" refString="Wu, Y-R, He, W, Wang, SF, 1988. Bee Fauna of Yunnan. Kunming, Yunnan Science and Technology Press" title="Bee Fauna of Yunnan." year="1988">Wu et al. 1988</bibRefCitation>
refer to other species, and the male of 
<taxonomicName id="51991A7301032B3D537391F6516314F7" genus="S." lsidName="S. grahami" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" rank="species" species="grahami">
<emphasis id="81CCD3AF5A87522328BFEAD854ABE620" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">S. grahami</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remains unknown. The female of this species is difficult to distinguish from the vicarious West-Palaearctic 
<taxonomicName id="7002F8BEC6414BC2DFA242A42E8D7EB5" genus="S." lsidName="S. ephippius" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" rank="species" species="ephippius">
<emphasis id="404D0E8143CA9502BA84586C5CE38C30" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">S. ephippius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken id="11CA674321717E8F953757ADBEB10737" originalValue="LinnÃ©">Linne</normalizedToken>
, 1767) and it is also similar to 
<taxonomicName id="9A394537E827BC26771E972FBB18C082" genus="S." lsidName="S. pellucidus subsp. var. var. gibridus" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" rank="variety" species="pellucidus" subSpecies="var." variety="gibridus">S. pellucidus var. gibridus</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="31D22A75127A8A53A793312A63EC5BAE" originalValue="BlÃ¼thgen">Bluethgen</normalizedToken>
, 1924. Clarification of the status of this species and possible synonymy is a task for future study.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5BA535F6BF35889F51291E9E79DA9E55" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="6CC0270E4F32981E6C96F062AD92A38C" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="623BA3800E9D1B8CE18C225729BE8FD6" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">
China (Shanxi, Shaanxi, Shanghai, Sichuan). The records by 
<bibRefCitation id="83B399A861A1B8D5A793AFBFCAED8230" author="Ascher, JS" journalOrPublisher="Zoologica Scripta" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" publicationUrl="http://www.discoverlife.org/mp/20q?guide=Apoidea_species" refId="B2" refString="Ascher, JS, Pickering, J, 2020. Discover Life bee species guide and world checklist (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Anthophila). http://www.discoverlife.org/mp/20q?guide=Apoidea_species" title="Discover Life bee species guide and world checklist (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Anthophila)." url="http://www.discoverlife.org/mp/20q?guide=Apoidea_species" year="2020">Ascher and Pickering 2020</bibRefCitation>
from Jilin, Hebei, Zhejiang, Anhui, Jiangsu, Yunnan, Xizang, Guandong based on misidentification that was published by 
<bibRefCitation id="00526361893B19A5F8BA40076D87A841" author="Wu, Y-R" journalOrPublisher="Sciense Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" refId="B25" refString="Wu, Y-R, 1965. Hymenoptera: Apoidea, Chinese Economic Insect Fauna, Vol. 9. Sciense Press, Beijing" title="Hymenoptera: Apoidea, Chinese Economic Insect Fauna, Vol. 9." year="1965">Wu (1965)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EE515EFF68EA9A62B4166ADE842B729E" author="Wu, Y-R" journalOrPublisher="Kunming, Yunnan Science and Technology Press" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" refId="B26" refString="Wu, Y-R, He, W, Wang, SF, 1988. Bee Fauna of Yunnan. Kunming, Yunnan Science and Technology Press" title="Bee Fauna of Yunnan." year="1988">Wu et al. (1988)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
